You need to add an EventCallback parameter to do that:

``` csharp
@code {

    [Parameter]
    public string Value { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    public EventCallback&lt;string&gt; ValueChanged { get; set; }
}
```

read the section [Data binding](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/blazor/components?view=aspnetcore-3.0#data-binding)/Component parameters

First solution:

* Define the pair Value and its companion ValueChanged event that matches the type of the Value parameter 

   ```
     [Parameter]
     public string Value { get; set; }
            
      [Parameter]
      public EventCallback&lt;string&gt; ValueChanged { get;set; }
```

* Add to the input tag a value attribute bound to the property Value like this:  `value=&quot;@Value&quot;`
Also add an @oninput directive whose value is a local method that is called whenever you type in the text box
 `@oninput=&quot;@OnValueChanged&quot;`

 Note that the method OnValueChanged updates the value of the Value property, and then invoke the ValueChanged EventCallback &#39;delegate&#39; in order to update the _value property defined in the parent component.

Note that the @bind directive is not used in this solution. In following solution I&#39;ll demonstrate how to use it.
                  

    


    form&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;label for=&quot;sampleText&quot;&gt;Sample Text&lt;/label&gt;
                    &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot;
                           class=&quot;form-control&quot;
                           id=&quot;sampleText&quot;
                           aria-describedby=&quot;sampleTextHelp&quot;
                           placeholder=&quot;Enter a text&quot;
                           value=&quot;@Value&quot;
               @oninput=&quot;@OnValueChanged&quot;  
                           /&gt;
                    &lt;small id=&quot;sampleTextHelp&quot; class=&quot;form-text text-muted&quot;&gt;Enter a text to test the databinding&lt;/small&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/form&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;You entered here: @Value&lt;/p&gt;
            
            @code {
               private string value;
            
            [Parameter]
            public string Value
            {
                get
                {
                    return this.value ?? &quot;&quot;;
                }
                set
                {
                    if (this.value!= value)
                    {
                        this.value= value;
                    }
                }
            }
                
                [Parameter]
                public string Value { get; set; }
               
                 [Parameter]
                public EventCallback&lt;string&gt; ValueChanged { get; set; }
            
               private Task OnValueChanged(ChangeEventArgs e)
            {
                Value = (string)e.Value;
                return ValueChanged.InvokeAsync(Value );
            }
            }  

**Usage:**

    &lt;MVVMTest bind-Value=&quot;@_value&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
        You entered in MVVMTest:
        @_value
    &lt;/p&gt;
    
    @code {
         public string _value  { get; set; }
       
    }

